race.description: Three Rivers Machinery Kate Smith Memorial Handicap
race.comment: IMASTATEMENT (11) progressive mare rewarded for her consistency when saluting over 1100m at Dubbo in fast time. Winning apprentice retains the ride and will prove hard to hold out. GLOWING RAPIDS (1) smart gelding with a handy record over this track and trip. Gripped on late with the 59.5kg when a narrow third over this trip at Bathurst. Winning apprentice hops back on and can get across from the awkward gate. Top-three player. NEVERMISTA (9) due for a change of luck and doesn't have to improve much to win this. Strong through the line when second over 1100m at Scone. Maps well and has solid claims. THIS ONE TIME (8) disappointed in Highway class two-back, then crossed from the wide gate when a narrow fourth over 1000m at Taree. Gets a better setup with the claim and sure to go close. SIMPLY BETTER (12) just over six weeks between runs when a poor last at Bathurst. Earlier runs had merit and stays in the calculations.
